    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Two Agencies Change Their Names</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliot</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fallon McElligott in Minneapolis changes its name to Fallon Worldwide (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Fallon McElligott in Minneapolis, part of Publicis S.A., has changed its name to Fallon Worldwide as part of a renaming of its various units. The offices of the advertising agency will be known as Fallon Minneapolis, Fallon New York and Fallon London. And Duffy Design and Interactive is being renamed Duffy, with individual offices also going by the names of the cities in which they are based. The McElligott in Fallon McElligott referred to co-founder Tom McElligott, who left in 1988.</p>
      </block>
